text:
```Welcome today, this is a wonderful day to run the step 3 script.

The deadline to process the step3 is 15th of August 16:00 CET.

You can find the guide how to do that here: <https://github.com/DLC-link/canton-onboarding-testnet/tree/step3/step3>

Schedule: We have 4 steps, which means only one remains after this. But the step 4 is time sensitive, which means that once we send out the step 4 we have 24 hour to finalize the whole onboarding.

We have two plans:

1. If everybody finishes the step 3, we reach out to you on Friday, whether you are available. If we can collect you all, we will send out the step 4 and ask you to do it. This will be between 15th of August 14:00 - 17:00 CET. Since you all did a great job on the previous steps, that is our estimation.
2. Since it is Friday and we know that Friday is usually fun day, if we can't collect you all, we will postpone the step 4 until Monday. On Monday morning we send out the step 4 and we hope we can finish everything in 24 hour.

If you need any help please let me know, so I can assist further.```
That was the message <@U088UV6MKFE>
This leaves us to decide whether we want to do the step4 tomorrow or not.
